{
  "texts": [
    "Valid reads were defined as reads that did not fit into either the Failed or Invalid bins.",
    "The Failed and Invalid reads were collected and analyzed for quality control purposes, and all subsequent analyses were performed on the Valid reads.",
    "Count data for valid reads was aggregated per sequence, per sample, and was stored in a pivot table format, with nucleotide sequences on the rows, and samples (Illumina barcodes) on the columns.",
    "Sequences not detected in samples were assigned a count of 0.",
    "Count data was reads-per-million (RPM) normalized to the sequencing depth of each sample (Illumina barcode) with:"
  ]
}